Obvious optimizations don't works in "inline if"
Try it (advanced mode):      alert(true == null ? a() : b());    EVER true != null, in this case, EVER will trigger b(), but we get:      alert(!0 == null ? a() : b());    Same for:      alert(true == false ? a() : b());    Real life use:      function sum(a, b){        return (a == true ? 2 : a) + b;      }      alert(sum(true, 1));    Results in:      alert((!0 == !0 ? 2 : 1) + 1);    But correct is:      alert(3);